The wind was n’t blowing in a direction that sent the rain into the room , but droplets still beaded the blinds closer to the bottom .  
The lights felt artificially bright , in contrast to how dark the clouds and sky were outside .   
The room was set up like a high school classroom , minus the ‘ class’ , no students , no mess , no bulletin board with scraps on it or whiteboard with weeks - old marks that had n’t been wiped away .  
