We arrived at the hill with the rocks .   
There was light overgrowth , a fairly loose distribution of trees for the fact that it was untamed wilderness , and thick grass .   
A surveying team had passed through at one point , and they had disturbed earth here and there , felled a few trees , and spray painted the face of one of the larger rocks before leaving .
A bit of a shame , but I could understand the need for a quick and easy label .   
No minerals or stone of any particular value here .
