I flew back and away , as she hauled herself in , and matched her general direction .   
It made for a tiny bit more slack .
She let go of me , and she pulled herself to a tree .   
From there , she moved to a roof .
Like a frog ’s tongue , snapping out , seizing something .   
But the frog went to the fly , rather than the other way around .   
To the branch , to the railing , to the fence , then to the chimney .
She was faster than me for short distances , and only a bit slower for the sustained movement .   
We did n’t have far to go ,
so she did pretty well at getting ahead of me .   
Only the escape from the fire escape had slowed her down .
