The white decorative    trim on the black fabric was missing , and I planned more ornamentation for my gloves , but the rest was intact .   
Spires of gold like my old tiara stood up at my shoulders , the middle - center of my breastplate , and decorated the armor around my legs and on my gloves .   
The decoration at my forehead was a weight that kept my hood down , and my hair draped out over my right shoulder .   
A protective mask hung from my belt , the curved surface resting around the curve of my thigh .   
I ’d don it if there was danger , and if I did n’t need to speak .
The costume had a weight to it .   
