The break got worse , twisting-
I canceled the Wretch and let him fall .
The uneasy , unsure satisfaction that came with finding a way forward had its backlash , ten times the negative for any positive I might have found in it .
He hit the ground and fell against my leg , which added to the pressure and the lack of elbow room .   
I used flight to keep myself upright , but people were pressing in , and I gave them a second ’s pause with my aura .   
It made them stop , staring , and little else .
Stop fighting me , Wretch .   
