But there was no wind , and I did n’t feel the cold anymore- cool air , but not cold .   
The ground had a glow to it , like there were dim lights just beneath the snow .   
That glow was more intense toward the edge of the circle .
A ring thirty feet in diameterand past those thirty feet , there was nothing .   
Some of the cars and trucks had been cut apart , but the cut pieces still stood .
Not white , not black , not gray or anything neutral .   
It made my head hurt to look at it and to think about it .
